<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-21T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/184: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-21T14:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 21,
                                        1922—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>208. Department approves your statement to Nansen as indicated in your
                            October 13, 11 a.m. through Embassy London that on grounds of humanity
                            this Government would of course welcome action by the Kemalists
                            authorities to permit Ottoman Greeks now held in Anatolia to rejoin
                            their families in Greece.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>